metadata.name: CTEEP - Companhia de Transmissão de Energia Elétrica Paulista S.A
metadata.description: CTEEP ? Companhia de Transmissão de Energia Elétrica Paulista S.A. engages in the electric power transmission business in Brazil. As of February 2, 2021, it had a total installed transformation capacity of 68,386 MVA together with transmission lines of 18,786 kilometers (km); 26,074 km of circuits; and 128 substations. It operates in the states of Rio Grande do Sul, Santa Catarina, Parana, Sao Paulo, Minas Gerais, Rondonia, Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul, Goias, Tocantins, Maranhao, Piaui, Paraiba, Pernambuco, Alagoas, Espirito Santo, and Bahia. The company was incorporated in 1999 and is headquartered in São Paulo, Brazil.
